```cpp
if (match(M1LHS, m_c_Add(m_Specific(X), m_One())) && M1RHS == Y)
```

It doesn't check for `or disjoint` with constant 1. For the `or disjoint` case, `or disjoint i32 %arg0, 1` is equivalent to `add nuw nsw i32 %arg0, 1` when the operands are disjoint (i.e., bit 0 of %arg0 is 0). The `disjoint` flag on `or` means the operands have no overlapping set bits.

So we need to also handle `or disjoint X, 1`. Let me check what the code should look like.

